      • onMessageReceived

        public static boolean onMessageReceived(android.content.Context context,
                        java.lang.String from,
                        android.os.Bundle data)
        Method to be called in your own Google Cloud Messaging GcmListenerService to handle WonderPush push notifications. Note: This is only required if you use your own GcmListenerService. Implement your GcmListenerService.onMessageReceived(String, Bundle) method as follows: 
        @Override
 public void onMessageReceived(String from, Bundle data) {
     if (WonderPushGcmListenerService.onMessageReceived(getApplicationContext(), from, data)) {
         return;
     }
     // Do your own handling here
 }
        Parameters:
        context - The current context
        from - The sender id
        data - The notification data
        Returns:
        Whether the notification has been handled by WonderPush
        See Also:
        WonderPush.onBroadcastReceived(Context, Intent, int, Class)

      • onMessageReceived

                        java.lang.String from,
                        android.os.Bundle data,
                        int iconResource,

        Method to be called in your own Google Cloud Messaging GcmListenerService to handle WonderPush push notifications, overriding default icon and default activity.

        from - The sender id
        data - The notification data
        iconResource - The default notification icon to use
        activity - The default activity to use
